rComments: Lectures were horrible not only bc of her accent, but bc she just read off the slides which anyone can do. Her exam questions were fine, at least. I recommend relying on any other resources except her lectures, bc they are just a waste of time.

Lectures were shorter than the other profs and her learning objectives were direct. I watched her lectures at 1.75x and had no issue understanding her since the diagrams and text on the slides clearly indicated what she wanted us to know. I liked that her lectures were straight to the point and I would love to have her again as prof in the future

I felt i just had to leave some nice comments cause ppl are being really harsh on her he accent is her only flaw otherwise she is clear concise and her testing is very very fair her material is always well understood she just happens to have a thick accent

Her thick accent is ok if u listen to her recordings at higher speed. Her exam questions were relatively straight-forward so I definitely appreciated that. She also tended to read off the slides so it was boring, but her lecture component itself was again straight-forward and rather easy to understand.

I really don't wanna be rude but I could barely understand her accent. I'm not a native speaker myself but I can understand most accents just fine. Her's however was really hard to decipher. Half the lecture slides I was unsure what she was saying. I basically had to teach myself the concepts from other sources. As a prof  I would not recommend her

I saw the reviews and felt compelled to write something nice. I think it is unfair to be so harsh about the accent. Dr Chen did a good job! Her exam questions were very straightforward! It does not take hours to go through a lecture, in fact, her lectures were never the 1h20 min length. People should be kinder, she was a good prof :)

She doesn't really contribute much except that lecture videos were already pre-recorded. Not to be rude but if you have trouble understanding an east-Asian accent when speaking English, get ready to read the textbooks. I could not understand her if I tried. A 40 min video will take me hours due to rewinding so much to understand what she is saying
